  "body": "Ethereum-Harmony exposes their RPC port on the same port that they expose their GUI on with the directory /rpc/\r\n\r\nE.G. http://harmony:8080/rpc/\r\n\r\nIt is impossible to add these nodes due to the current method that MyCrypto adds custom nodes (by appending the port number to the URI).\r\n\r\nIf the port number was optional, or just removed and specified in the URL this would allow the adding of Ethereum-Harmony nodes.\r\n\r\nI should be able to just put `http://harmony:8080/rpc/` into the URL field. I'm don't think having a separate port field is better than just asking users to add nodes with the URL format of `http://hostname:8545'",
