    "body": "Yup, this was a really naive first pass for custom nodes. I'd had a note to replace this with a more robust URL creator, but it hadn't come up yet. Thanks for reminding me of the demand, I can take a crack at this shortly.\r\n\r\nI think you're right that a straight-forward URL input will probably do the job, as long as helpful messages are added when users make mistakes or do unintuitive things, e.g. remind them to add http/s protocol, or inform them that it will default to 80 / 443 if they don't specify a port.",
